text: Alexela Concert Hall (, earlier Nokia Concert Hall ()) is a concert hall in Tallinn, Estonia. The hall is located adjacent to Solaris Center. The hall's owner is Tallinna Kontserdimaja AS. The hall was constructed from 2007–2009. The hall consists of 1,829 seats as follows: 1,030 in the arena, 491 in the dress circle and 308 in the upper circle. Several international events has been taken place there: e.g. 23rd European Film Awards in 2010. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Concert halls in Estonia Category:Buildings and structures in Tallinn
